channel.description:
[b]Originally Posted by theman12345[/b]
Running Aryan Using a Proxy
[b]Please read the WHOLE tut before asking questions.[/b]
If there are any questions, comments, corrections please post here or msg me
I do not take responsibility for your actions and any accounts banned. The files should be clean but scan first before downloading. If they have spy-ware contact me and I will remove them, I will also remove broken links.
EDITS: 2-04-06 Fixed little error 1-4-06 Re-Wrote a few things 25-3-06 Starting adding proxy lists 19-3-06 Added more links 13-3-06 Re-Wrote some things 10-3-06 Minor changes, Re-Wrote some things 27-2-06 Added More links 25-2-06 Added Pictures 25-2-06 Made Tut
[b]--CONTENTS:--[/b] Introduction What does this have to do with Proxies? Where do I get a Socks 5 proxy? What do I do with the Proxy now? Problems More Information
[size=14][b]--INTRODUCTION--[/b][/size]
When you use the Internet, Surf sites and Play epacsenur etc, a thing called your IP(Internet Protocol) Address is sent to the websites and to Jagex when playing epacsenur. This IP Address is unique for every computer connected to the Internet. This can be used to trace which country you are from and who your ISP (Internet Service Provider) is. Further-more, it lets Jagex know what accounts are being played from the same IP address. This is bad. This means Jagex can link your main to your bots if you don't take action.
[b]--WHAT DOES THIS HAVE TO DO WITH PROXIES?--[/b]
A proxy is a server that acts as a shield to stop websites seeing your REAL IP Address. Instead of sending data straight to the website, it goes through a proxy, so the proxy's IP Address is shown. There are different types of proxies, but the one we need for Aryan is SOCKS5 proxies, not 4, not elite. This is because SOCKS 5 are the only proxies compatible with epacsenur and that Jagex can see your IP through all the other type except SOCKS5. Also, we must test it because some proxies don't work :( .
[b]--WHERE DO I GET A SOCKS 5 PROXY?--[/b]
There are a number of Freeware and Shareware programs available that find and test proxies. Also, we can search Google and find proxy lists (lists of proxies) and use a proxy checker to check them. I suggest regularly checking them, as arenâ€™t reliable and donâ€™t work after a while. You can download a free proxy checker or use an online proxy checker.

There's ALOT more out there, just search Google
[b]--WHAT DO I DO WITH THE PROXY NOW?--[/b]
OK, you have got a working SOCKS5 proxy, now its time to use it.
Go to where your Aryan folder is and right click on Run-Bot and then click edit. You will see something like this:
[code] @echo off title Running Bot java -noverify -Xmx500m -cp .;./OUTPUT;./OUTPUT/unrenamed.jar;./BotClasses;./LIB; Bot %1 pause[/code]
Delete it all and replace with this: [code] @echo off title Running Bot java -DsocksProxyHost=12.345.678.910 -DsocksProxyPort=1234 -noverify -Xmx500m -cp .;./OUTPUT;./OUTPUT/unrenamed.jar;./BotClasses; Bot pause[/code]
Now you have two options:
1) You press save to overwrite the Run-Bot file
2)Or if you want to make a new .bat file put this in: Now press save as and call it proxybot.bat or whatever, make sure the save as type is all files and that you have .bat after the file name.
Replace the stuff in bold with the Socks5 IP in the first part, and in the second part put in the Port. ,
Now when you want to play Aryan you click on the .bat file that you put the new code in, this will run Aran through the Proxy. Enjoy proxying :)
[b]--PROBLEMS--[/b]
Q: I get Error connecting to Server when I go to Log in, how do I get rid of this? A: You probably need a new proxy, or you have problems connecting to that one, or your code isnâ€™t correct
Q: I get error Downloading News A: Your proxy doesnâ€™t work, try a different one. If the problem persists, check your code
Q: When click Run-Bot , I get Connection error - Retrying in 20secs, or E02 Error A: Check to see your Code is correct, and check the proxy again. If the problem still happens, Use a different proxy.
Q: I can't find any proxies, where do I get One: A: Scroll up and read "Where do I get a SOCKS5 proxy?"
Q: I used your proxy IP: 12.345.678.910 PORT: 1234, and It doesn't work, Help!! A: This shouldn't be a proxy, and it isn't one. This is used as an example: lol: ,find your own!!

item.title: [TUT]Running Aryan Using a Proxy[TUT]
item.dc:creator: @bob bob
item.description:
@bob wrote:

Request a new IP address from your ISP server.

Here’s how to do it in windows:

  1. Click Start
  2. Click run
  3. In the run box type cmd.exe and click OK
  4. When the command prompt opens type the following. ENTER after each new line.

ipconfig /flushdns ipconfig /release ipconfig /renew exit
5. Erase your cookies in whatever browser you are using.

Frequently you will be assigned a new IP address when this happens. Sometime you will, sometimes you will not. If you are on a fixed IP address, this method will not work. To be honest, I do not know how to do this in linux/unix/etc. If this works for you, you may want to save the above commands into a batch file, and just run it when you need it.

To make a batch file for you noobs copy and paste the following into a notepad file:

ipconfig /flushdns iponfig /release ipconfig /renew exit
File>>Save As “Whatever.bat”
